Description: Online Intelligence provides brand protection and traffic integrity services to premiere advertising clients.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Online Intelligence, L.L.C. ("OI"), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Epic Advertising Inc., provides brand protection and traffic integrity services to Epic's advertising clients. The OI technology and team afford advertisers visibility into the online ad sequence and provide monitoring for off-brand placements and prohibited content associations. OI builds on Epic's 8+ years of experience in formulating compliance strategies and examining traffic patterns across a global network of more than 45,000 marketers and publishers. The heart of OI is its compliance tool: an integrated, SaaS software program that allows the team to delve into the sources of web traffic for Epic's clients. Through a complex system of proactive web-crawling, OI can monitor an advertiser's campaign in real-time. The goal for Epic's clients: whether the advertiser is concerned about incentivized traffic, malware, content associations, or "negative keywords", the OI team can identify the infraction and move to redress. In June, 2009, Epic drafted former Director of Security Enforcement at Fox Interactive Media (MySpace) E.J. Hilbert to lead OI's efforts. Prior to joining MySpace, E.J. was a Special Agent with the Federal Bureau of Investigation. In that capacity, E.J. investigated all aspects of cybercrime, including but not limited to piracy, "phishing", spam, DDOS, identity theft, malware and spyware, and wire fraud. E.J. is a CISSP (Certified Information Systems Security Professional), and has accrued more than 700 hours of training in computer forensics, forensic accounting, and advanced computer intrusion techniques. Supporting E.J. are OI's Chairman, David Graff, an attorney with several years of corporate and public company compliance experience, and OI's Chief Privacy Officer, Anwesa Paul, an attorney and CIPP (Certified Information Privacy Professional).
Industry Groups: Advertising, Privacy and Security, Sales and Marketing, Software

Description: Mapfia is a mobile application that allows users to share their location with others.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: [Mapfia](http://www.mapfia.com) is an application for [iPhone](http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mapfia/id530029108?ls=1&mt=8) and [Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mapfia.android) phones that lets you make free “map calls”. When you call another Mapfia user and the call is answered, you can see each other’s real time location on a map. **_"Need to share your location...I don’t think I’ve seen an easier method than Mapfia"_** - [ GigaOM](http://bit.ly/LfbFlP)  **_"As check-ins and similar features become a more frequent feature of social media...Mapfia is taking the initiative to offer users more control over their data."_** - [Springwise.com](http://bit.ly/NzTUND)     **Why Mapfia?** Come on, do you really want your friends and coworkers to see your location 24/7 once you accept their friend requests? Do you have the time to send an SMS or an email to get directions when you are lost or running late? You need a simple and secure way to share location, and that’s where we come in. With Mapfia, you can see each other’s location just by making a quick phone call, and once you hang up, that’s it! It only shares your location privately while you are on the call. Mapfia also integrates seamlessly with your existing address book and does not require a PIN or username. Our goal is to make navigation and location sharing easy and secure with our patented technology.

Description: Nsoma is dedicated to solving the challenges of education at the intersection of programming and technology.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: We are a company dedicated to solving the challenges of education at the intersection of programming and technology, which is a confusing arena.  When researching names, we found that many companies use words like integrate, interface, and connect in education.  And yet, back-end systems are still confusing and do not work together.  So what, truly, is being connected?   We looked for something different.  In Uganda, the Lugandan language is spoken as it is written.  "Nsoma" is one word that is a full sentence, meaning  "I read."  It is simple and direct, but also a full thought.  The solutions to complex problems must also be simple or they will not really be solutions.   We believe that if you want things to connect, you need to connect them.  But that's often more easily said than done.  This is our mission to find the solutions that link technologies, reducing the complexity faced by schools and universities.

Description: Destination: Home is a public-private partnership serving as the backbone organization for collective impact strategies to end homelessness.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Destination: Home is a public-private partnership serving as the backbone organization for collective impact strategies to end homelessness in Santa Clara County. It was established in 2008 as an outcome of a Blue Ribbon Commission on ending homelessness led by then San Jose Mayor Chuck Reed and then County Supervisor Don Gage. In 2011 Destination: Home became a program of the Health Trust and in 2013 took on the role of Santa Clara County’s Continuum of Care (CoC) Board.  In this role as the local CoC Board, Destination: Home has worked with regional partners to develop a new five year Community Plan to End Homelessness.  In late 2017 the Destination: Home leadership board voted to move Destination: Home from being a project of The Health Trust to a Supporting Organization under the umbrella of the Silicon Valley Community Foundation.  Read our FAQs regarding our move to become a Supporting Organization here. The Community Plan addresses public system disruption to enhance services and efficiency, creating more housing opportunities in our land and housing-scarce community and ensuring the appropriate housing interventions and case management resources are available for unique populations, including preventative measures. This Community Plan is based on a proof of concept collective impact campaign, Housing 1000, which uses a nationally recognized Housing First model that focuses on getting clients into housing as quickly as possible and provides supportive services to ensure recovery, stability, and a decrease of public systems usage. Destination: Home drives and aligns resources to create permanent housing and sustainable support systems built for the long term. The organization is improving how systems work together to end homelessness, as well as protect individuals and families at risk of becoming homeless. In this role, Destination: Home’s Board also serves as the HUD Continuum of Care Board for the San Jose /Santa Clara City and County Metropolitan area and works with the Santa Clara County Office of Supportive Housing as a Collaborative Applicant to expand local allocations of federal funding.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Other, Social Impact
